This paper is primarily focused on face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also discusses the use of large-scale unlabeled video data and the transfer of knowledge from still images, which suggests that it may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper utilizes synthetic data augmentation, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research. The use of a domain adversarial discriminator also suggests that the paper may fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
